# Tailwind CSS Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind v4 Usage

-   Use Tailwind CSS v4 classes for all styling
-   Leverage the new color system and design tokens
-   Use semantic color names when possible
-   Follow mobile-first responsive design

## Class Organization

-   Group related classes logically: layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects
-   Use consistent spacing scale: `p-4`, `m-2`, `gap-3`
-   Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
-   Use component variants for repeated patterns

## Common Patterns

```tsx
// Good: Logical class grouping
<div className="
  flex flex-col gap-4 p-6
  bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md
  border border-gray-200
  hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow
">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
    Habit Tracker
  </h2>
  <p className="text-gray-600">
    Track your daily habits
  </p>
</div>

// Good: Responsive design
<div className="
  grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3
  gap-4 md:gap-6 lg:gap-8
">
```

## Color System

-   Use semantic colors: `text-gray-900`, `bg-blue-500`
-   Maintain consistent color palette across components
-   Use opacity modifiers: `bg-blue-500/10`
-   Follow accessibility guidelines for contrast

## Component Variants

-   Create reusable button, card, and input styles
-   Use consistent spacing and sizing
-   Maintain visual hierarchy through typography and spacing
